The Eiffel Tower is located in Paris, France. The Eiffel Tower was completed in 1889. The Eiffel Tower is 324 meters tall. The Eiffel Tower was designed by Gustave Eiffel.
The Great Wall of China is over 13,000 miles long. The Great Wall of China began construction in the 7th century BC. The Great Wall of China was built to protect against invasions from northern tribes. The Great Wall of China is a UNESCO World Heritage site.
The Taj Mahal is located in Agra, India. The Taj Mahal was built by Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife Mumtaz Mahal. The Taj Mahal's construction started in 1632 and was completed in 1653. The Taj Mahal is made of white marble.
Moscow is the capital city of Russia. Moscow is the largest city in Europe by population. The Moscow Metro, opened in 1935, is one of the busiest metro systems in the world. Red Square is a famous landmark in Moscow.
The Colosseum is located in Rome, Italy. The Colosseum was completed in AD 80. The Colosseum could hold up to 80,000 spectators. The Colosseum was used for gladiatorial contests and public spectacles.
The Statue of Liberty is located in New York City, USA. The Statue of Liberty was a gift from France to the United States. The Statue of Liberty was dedicated on October 28, 1886. The Statue of Liberty is 93 meters tall from the ground to the tip of the torch.